  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-based ecotourism in the Kafa Biosphere Reserve</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Community-based ecotourism in the Kafa Biosphere Reserve</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Host organization NABU (The Nature and Biodiversity Conservation Union) is dedicated to protecting biodiversity, promoting sustainable development, protected areas, community-minded programs on conservation and environmental education. The tasks of the volunteer will include: - Become familiar with already existing tourist infrastructure, local initiatives and strategies Kafa Biosphere Reserve - Promote the development of infrastructure (eg museum, information center) - Assist local communities in activities related to tourism - Assist in the development of new initiatives and programs - To raise general awareness of the need to preserve this unique ecosystem</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Hostite&#x13E;sk&#xE1; organiz&#xE1;cia NABU (The Nature and Biodiversity Conservation Union) sa venuje ochrane biodiverzity, podpore trvalo udr&#x17E;ate&#x13E;n&#xE9;ho rozvoja, chr&#xE1;nen&#xFD;ch oblast&#xED;, komunitne zameran&#xFD;m programom na ochranu pr&#xED;rody a environment&#xE1;lnemu vzdel&#xE1;vaniu. Projekty v Eti&#xF3;pii a oblasti Kafa podporuje od roku 2006. Medzi &#xFA;lohy dobrovo&#x13E;n&#xED;ka bude patri&#x165;: - zozn&#xE1;mi&#x165; sa s u&#x17E; existuj&#xFA;cou turistickou infra&#x161;trukt&#xFA;rou, lok&#xE1;lnymi iniciat&#xED;vami a strat&#xE9;giami v biosf&#xE9;rickej rezerv&#xE1;cii Kafa - podpori&#x165; rozvoj tejto infra&#x161;trukt&#xFA;ry (napr. m&#xFA;zeum v pr&#xED;rode, informa&#x10D;n&#xE9; centrum) - asistova&#x165; lok&#xE1;lnym komunit&#xE1;m pri aktivit&#xE1;ch t&#xFD;kaj&#xFA;cich sa cestovn&#xE9;ho ruchu - napom&#xE1;ha&#x165; pri rozvoji nov&#xFD;ch iniciat&#xED;v a programov - zvy&#x161;ova&#x165; v&#x161;eobecn&#xE9; povedomie o potrebe zachovania tohto jedine&#x10D;n&#xE9;ho ekosyst&#xE9;mu</narrative>
  </description>
